{"id": "duc04-testb-23:6#18", "contents": "Leaders from 19 Latin American nations, Spain and Portugal gathered on Saturday to finalize a declaration for the Ibero-American summit, warning of a potential global recession if the international financial system is not stabilized. The draft declaration emphasized the need for swift action to prevent the difficulties affecting a few countries from becoming a crisis for all. This declaration is addressed to the world's seven richest nations, collectively known as the Group of Seven, which comprises the United States, Japan, Britain, Germany, France, Italy, and Canada."}
